  "raw_response": "```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Consolidation Failure on ETH 1-Hour: Closure Through Down-Close Candle Without V-Shape Recovery\",\n  \"school\": \"ICT\",\n  \"asset\": \"ETH\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"1H\",\n  \"market_context\": \"ETH 1-hour chart showing a peak near 83200 followed by a downward sequence. Price retraced into a fair value gap after a V-shaped reversal lower, and the analyst is evaluating whether a closure through the down-close candle constitutes a valid continuation entry.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"Price did close over the down-close candle, but instead of doing so with a swift V-shape, it formed a consolidation. The closure ultimately just swept the consolidation high to trade lower, rather than confirming a bullish continuation.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: Identify the prior V-shaped reversal lower and the fair value gap left by the displacement, marking the area as a potential continuation point of interest.\",\n    \"Step 2: Look for a closure through the single down-close candle into that fair value gap as the continuation trigger.\",\n    \"Step 3: Observe that the closure does occur, but note it lacks swift V-shape price action — price stalls and forms a consolidation around the level.\",\n    \"Step 4: Recognize the closure is actually sweeping the high of the consolidation range rather than initiating a true continuation.\",\n    \"Step 5: Conclude that the setup should be treated as consolidation, staying sidelined to avoid the loss that follows as price trades lower.\"\n  ],\n  \"outcome\"",
